cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper proposes a new consensus scheme for blockchains that utilizes computational resources for machine learning optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses privacy-preserving blockchain mining and Sybil resistance. The second most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on using computational resources for machine learning optimization. The third likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper discusses a decentralized approach to machine learning competitions. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper discusses the optimization of machine learning models. The fifth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper discusses the interaction between data providers, miners, and a committee in the proposed consensus scheme.
